It’s been a year of stepping into the shoes of Raavi, and today, 
I can say that she feels almost like home.
Like second nature. Like muscle memory. She’s the art that just flows within me. ✨🌸

A mirror that knows me all too well, she’s has become a reflection that is all too familiar. 
So much of what I am exists in the form of her. And everything that she is, is entrenched in me because I’ve gotten a lot more back from her. Like two beings experiencing oneness and falling in love with it because of each other, we now live and breathe together. 

It all began with adding little things to her. Like the myriad of emotions behind her words. Or a hundred different shades dissolved in her laughter. Like the spectrum of sadness she braved through as she cried. Or the distinct ways in which she expressed anger. Her many nuances, her many nazakats. All her quirks, all her harkats. Unite to become her. ❤️

This is how she was brought to life from paper—bit by bit, piece by piece and chapter by chapter. 
And after a whole year, this is exactly what makes playing 
Raavi all the more fulfilling and fun. 
So much so, that it’s not this way or that way anymore, 
it’s Raavi’s way, and that’s how we roll and make it work! 😌🎥

Here’s to adding many more layers to the person I have come to discover and treasure. She’s mine but at the same time, she belongs to so many who’ve given her nothing but unconditional love! 

#ThankfulToTheT 
#OneYearOfPlayingMyFavourite #RaaviIsMe #RaaviIsYou #ILoveYouGuys ❤️❤️❤️❤️
